00:29:01.360 --> 00:29:02.370
Um, all right.

00:29:02.370 --> 00:29:03.948
We&#39;ll skip a little bit of
this.

00:29:03.948 --> 00:29:04.848
All right.

00:29:06.842 --> 00:29:09.830
So, now we&#39;re gonna talk
about execution.

00:29:09.830 --> 00:29:13.650
Um, execution for most
founders is

00:29:13.650 --> 00:29:15.850
not the more fun part of
starting a company.

00:29:15.850 --> 00:29:17.850
But it is often the most
critical.

00:29:17.850 --> 00:29:20.900
Um, most people that start a
company think that they

00:29:20.900 --> 00:29:23.630
are signing up to have this
brilliant idea.

00:29:23.630 --> 00:29:25.340
And, you know, then they&#39;re
just going to be,

00:29:25.340 --> 00:29:26.870
like, be on magazine covers
and go to parties.

00:29:28.493 --> 00:29:30.483
&gt;&gt; But really what it&#39;s
about more than

00:29:30.483 --> 00:29:33.563
anything else, what, what
being a founder means is, is

00:29:33.563 --> 00:29:36.642
signing up for this year&#39;s
long grind on execution, and

00:29:36.642 --> 00:29:38.200
you can&#39;t outsource this.

00:29:39.240 --> 00:29:42.160
Um, the way to have a
company that executes well

00:29:42.160 --> 00:29:43.830
is to execute well yourself.

