Everything in startup gets
modeled after the founders.

00:29:47.310 --> 00:29:49.409
Whatever the founders do
becomes the culture.

00:29:49.409 --> 00:29:51.705
So if you want a culture
where people work hard and

00:29:51.705 --> 00:29:54.169
pay attention to detail and
focus on the customer and

00:29:54.169 --> 00:29:54.897
are frugal um,

00:29:54.897 --> 00:29:57.148
you have to do it yourself
there is no other way.

00:29:57.148 --> 00:29:59.644
You cannot hire a COO and
have them, you know,

00:29:59.644 --> 00:30:01.827
do this while you go off to
conferences.

00:30:01.827 --> 00:30:03.597
The company just needs to
see you as

00:30:03.597 --> 00:30:05.680
like this maniacal execution
machine.

00:30:07.050 --> 00:30:08.140
As I said in the first
lecture,

00:30:08.140 --> 00:30:10.890
there&#39;s like a hundred times
at least more people with

00:30:10.890 --> 00:30:11.580
great ideas.

00:30:11.580 --> 00:30:13.920
Than people that are willing
to put in the effort,

00:30:13.920 --> 00:30:15.110
um, to execute them well.

